Whatever the Herald has is circumstantial.

353
00:21:45,210 --> 00:21:46,200
当然
Of course.

354
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:48,320
没人知道她到底遭遇了什么
No one knows what really happened to her,

355
00:21:48,320 --> 00:21:49,640
永远也不会有人知道
and no one ever will.

356
00:21:52,290 --> 00:21:53,680
是这样  道格
But, look, Doug...

357
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:57,270
今晚我和克莱尔请你来的原因
The reason that Claire and I invited you over tonight

358
00:21:57,270 --> 00:22:01,290
是因为我们希望你知道你对我们多么重要
is because we want you to know how much you mean to us.

359
00:22:01,290 --> 00:22:02,700
对我们两个都是
To both of us.

360
00:22:04,250 --> 00:22:05,310
好  先生
Yes, sir.

361
00:22:05,310 --> 00:22:06,720
在我们说别的事之前
Before we say anything else,

362
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:09,710
我们只想明白无误地确认
we just wanted to be absolutely certain that...

363
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,810
你知道这一点
you knew that.

364
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,190
当然
Of course.

365
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:19,780
我们要面临的
What we're up against,

366
00:22:19,790 --> 00:22:22,770
这个政府要面临的
what this administration is facing...

367
00:22:22,770 --> 00:22:23,730
也是我要面临的
Well, what I'm facing...

368
00:22:23,730 --> 00:22:25,660
即便我们都相信
Even though both of us believe that

369
00:22:25,670 --> 00:22:28,540
我被起诉的可能微乎其微
there's very little chance that I could ever be indicted,

370
00:22:28,550 --> 00:22:30,010
我们仍然
we still...

371
00:22:30,650 --> 00:22:31,760
得想办法
have to find a way to

372
00:22:31,760 --> 00:22:34,780
彻底解决这整件事
remove this entire issue from the table.

373
00:22:34,780 --> 00:22:38,270
我不能再跟这事有牵连了
I just can no longer be associated with this.

374
00:22:38,780 --> 00:22:41,690
我会辞职  并继续处理此事
I'll resign while I'm dealing with this.

375
00:22:44,990 --> 00:22:48,290
我觉得这可能还不够
I think this is going to require more than that.

376
00:22:48,770 --> 00:22:51,220
我会发表声明
Well, I'll make a statement...

377
00:22:51,630 --> 00:22:54,090
说这是人身攻击式的政治手段
and blame it on the politics of personal destruction.

378
00:22:54,100 --> 00:22:57,730
不  道格  恐怕这些仍不够
No, Doug, I'm afraid that's just not going to be enough.

379
00:22:59,190 --> 00:23:03,160
我们得转移怀疑目标
We have to shift... the suspicion.

380
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:06,570
我们需要你...
We need you to...

381
00:23:06,570 --> 00:23:10,470
我们需要你让自己跟佐伊·巴恩斯的死挂上钩
We need you to implicate yourself in the death of Zoe Barnes.

382
00:23:10,470 --> 00:23:12,740
先别激动  听我说
Now, before you react, just listen.

383
00:23:12,740 --> 00:23:14,070
目前你是最有可能的人选
You are the most likely candidate at this point.

384
00:23:14,070 --> 00:23:16,130
你当时心烦意乱  还酗酒
You were distraught, you were drinking.

385
00:23:16,140 --> 00:23:17,520
我说不好
The... I don't know.

386
00:23:17,520 --> 00:23:19,490
我们会编一些事出来  然后泄漏出去
We'll make up some story, and then we'll leak it.

387
00:23:19,490 --> 00:23:21,460
你忠心耿耿  你那么做是为了我
You... you were loyal, you did it for me.

388
00:23:21,460 --> 00:23:24,680
你忠诚过了头  采取了极端手段
You were too loyal. You went too far.

389
00:23:24,680 --> 00:23:27,730
然后  到最后  毫无疑问
And... and then, in the end, there'll be no question...

390
00:23:27,730 --> 00:23:29,320
我失陪一下好吗
Can you excuse me?

391
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:11,520
生日快乐

392
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:32,360
这要么是哪个怪胎想搏头条
Well, it's either a crank looking for a headline,

393
00:24:32,370 --> 00:24:34,860
要么就是内部人士在说真话
or someone on the inside telling the truth.

394
00:24:34,860 --> 00:24:35,990
你感觉是什么
What's your sense?

395
00:24:35,990 --> 00:24:37,840
他知道生日卡的事
He knew about the birthday cards.

396
00:24:38,390 --> 00:24:39,590
我说不好
I don't know.

397
00:24:39,850 --> 00:24:41,610
也许重点在于这电话
Maybe the story is the call.

398
00:24:41,820 --> 00:24:43,460
那些闪存盘  泄密本身
The flash drives. The leaks themselves.

399
00:24:43,460 --> 00:24:45,020
如果我们点出泄密的事
If we call out the leaks,

400
00:24:45,020 --> 00:24:46,420
他可能就不会再联系我了
he may stop contacting me.

401
00:24:46,420 --> 00:24:49,350
还有麦卡伦的事  那真是条线索吗
And the Macallan business, is that even a real lead?

402
00:24:49,350 --> 00:24:51,180
这些网站什么都不会承认的
None of these sites will admit to anything.

403
00:24:51,180 --> 00:24:52,830
因为这太丢人了
Because it's an embarrassment.

404
00:24:52,890 --> 00:24:55,180
多个选情对安德伍德不利的郡的
An overwhelming amount of Underwood material

405
00:24:55,180 --> 00:24:57,830
社交媒体用户  爆出了大量
was reported by social media users in counties

406
00:24:57,830 --> 00:24:59,780
安德伍德的材料
that he was expected to lose.

407
00:24:59,780 --> 00:25:01,040
但我联系的所有人
But anyone I reach out to

408
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:02,890
都不想谈论此事
does not wanna be talking about this.

409
00:25:02,890 --> 00:25:05,790
泄密者说那是未经授权的国内监控
The leak said it was unauthorized domestic surveillance.

410
00:25:05,790 --> 00:25:07,580
政府只需要搬出"恐怖活动"
All the administration has to say is "terror,"

411
00:25:07,580 --> 00:25:09,350
看起来就正当了
And they seem justified.

412
00:25:09,510 --> 00:25:11,960
他可不是在铲除恐怖分子
He wasn't rooting out terrorists.

413
00:25:11,960 --> 00:25:13,660
他是想赢得选举
He was trying to win an election.

414
00:25:13,660 --> 00:25:16,170
国务卿正好撞了头可太巧了
And very convenient that the Secretary of State hits her head.

415
00:25:16,170 --> 00:25:17,490
你现在听起来像是阴谋论...
Now you sound like a conspiracy...

416
00:25:17,490 --> 00:25:20,320
我不是阴谋论者
I'm not a conspiracy theorist.

417
00:25:20,390 --> 00:25:22,990
我试图想象他是怎么想的
I try to imagine what it's like inside his mind,

418
00:25:22,990 --> 00:25:24,940
如果我是他  我会怎么做
what I would do if I were him.

419
00:25:24,940 --> 00:25:28,530
我跟你们说  这是各种...
And I'm telling you, it is all sorts of...

420
00:25:30,390 --> 00:25:34,740
他没有意识形态  没有道德方向
He has no ideology. No North Star.

421
00:25:34,740 --> 00:25:37,320
这难道不是最可怕的吗
Isn't that the scariest thing of all?

422
00:25:37,320 --> 00:25:40,780
汤姆  你觉得佐伊·巴恩斯是被谋杀的吗
Tom, do you think Zoe Barnes was murdered?

423
00:25:40,900 --> 00:25:43,910
一个27岁的人失足撞上火车的概率有多大
How often does a 27-year-old fall in front of a train?

424
00:25:43,910 --> 00:25:47,120
-那好吧  我们去证明它  -好
- All right, then. Let's prove that. - All right.

425
00:25:56,520 --> 00:25:57,430
怎么了
What's wrong?

426
00:25:58,140 --> 00:25:59,460
道格·斯坦普的办公室来电了
Doug Stamper's office called.

427
00:25:59,460 --> 00:26:01,020
他们想安排见面
They wanna set up a meeting.

428
00:26:01,020 --> 00:26:02,300
尽快吧
Soon as possible.

429
00:26:04,220 --> 00:26:05,310
这是好事
This is good.

430
00:26:06,460 --> 00:26:10,010
不管你男友今早从你手机里读到了什么
Whatever your boyfriend read off your phone this morning

431
00:26:10,550 --> 00:26:12,320
都传到了正确的人的耳朵里
made its way to the right person.

432
00:26:13,020 --> 00:26:15,290
我不知道我还能坚持多久
I don't know how much longer I can do this.

433
00:26:16,970 --> 00:26:19,760
你只是在骗一个骗子
You're lying to a liar.

434
00:26:20,230 --> 00:26:22,930
你无法从佐伊死时的手机上得到任何信息
You can't get anything off the phone Zoe died with.

435
00:26:22,930 --> 00:26:25,190
他们只要相信我们能做到就行了
They just need to believe we can.

436
00:26:25,940 --> 00:26:27,560
这到底是什么工作
What is this job?

437
00:26:30,900 --> 00:26:32,350
跟以前不一样了
Not what it used to be.

438
00:26:40,460 --> 00:26:42,720
我不希望你反应过度
I don't want you to overreact.

439
00:26:43,070 --> 00:26:45,000
但汤姆一直在继续写作
But Tom kept writing.

440
00:26:45,150 --> 00:26:47,680
看来他终于完成他的书了
It seems he finally finished his book.

441
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:50,740
而且他暗示了一些事
And he alludes to things.

442
00:26:51,330 --> 00:26:53,270
什么叫"暗示了一些事"
What do you mean "Alludes to things"?

443
00:26:53,270 --> 00:26:54,510
我不知道  相关行都被涂黑了
I don't know. Lines are blacked out.

444
00:26:54,510 --> 00:26:55,430
就像被编辑过
It's like it's redacted.

445
00:26:55,430 --> 00:26:57,400
时不时的有一些段落
There are paragraphs here and there...

446
00:26:58,530 --> 00:26:59,830
你跟他说过什么
What did you tell him?

447
00:27:01,650 --> 00:27:02,840
他知道些什么
What does he know?

448
00:27:03,410 --> 00:27:05,090
他给任何人看过吗  寄给过任何人吗
Has he shown this to anyone? Sent it to anyone?

449
00:27:05,090 --> 00:27:06,880
-出版商  媒体  -我不知道
- Publishers, the press? - I don't know.

450
00:27:06,880 --> 00:27:08,440
那你知道什么
Well, what do you know?

451
00:27:09,740 --> 00:27:12,550
我来处理他  我只是想跟你说一声
I will handle him. I just wanted you to be aware.

452
00:27:12,550 --> 00:27:14,950
-妈了个逼的  -我说了我会处理的
- Son of a bitch. - I said I'll take care of it.

453
00:27:14,950 --> 00:27:16,100
不  我来处理
No, I'll take care of it.

454
00:27:16,100 --> 00:27:18,440
你躲得远远的
You stay a million miles away from this.

455
00:27:26,780 --> 00:27:28,820
你怎么会这么蠢
How could you be so stupid...

456
00:27:31,330 --> 00:27:33,070
动了真情
to fall in love?

457
00:27:34,810 --> 00:27:36,290
这事还没提交表决
This thing isn't on the floor yet,

458
00:27:36,290 --> 00:27:37,310
我们就已经失去参议员的支持了
and we're losing senators.

459
00:27:37,310 --> 00:27:38,940
失去了几个吧  不过
We're losing some maybe, but...

460
00:27:40,230 --> 00:27:42,720
参院最讨喜的地方也是我最讨厌的地方
What I like about the Senate is what I hate.

461
00:27:43,230 --> 00:27:44,410
传染性
It's contagious.

462
00:27:44,420 --> 00:27:45,390
只要一个人有了什么想法
One of 'em gets an idea,

463
00:27:45,390 --> 00:27:47,620
立马就会像流感一样传遍全院
and it spreads through the body like a flu.

464
00:27:47,620 --> 00:27:48,880
我再想想办法
I'll look into it.

465
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,880
总共就100个人  我们只需要过半
There's 100 of 'em. All we need is half.

466
00:27:54,120 --> 00:27:55,460
我能躺下吗
Can I just lay down?

467
00:27:55,460 --> 00:27:57,660
-最好不要  -我就躺几分钟
- I don't think that's a good idea. - Just for a few minutes.

468
00:27:57,660 --> 00:28:01,210
我他妈快累死了  我得想想
I'm just so fucking tired, and I need to think.

469
00:28:03,340 --> 00:28:04,710
你得想什么
Why do you need to think?

470
00:28:08,150 --> 00:28:10,130
他给你的那些东西  你拿在手里越久
The longer you hang on to whatever he gave you,

471
00:28:10,130 --> 00:28:11,770
你的处境就越危险
the more danger you're in.

472
00:28:11,860 --> 00:28:13,450
你错看局势了
You're reading this wrong.

473
00:28:14,010 --> 00:28:16,630
你以为那是保险  其实不是
You think it's some kind of insurance, but it's not.

474
00:28:18,470 --> 00:28:19,380
莉安
LeAnn...

475
00:28:19,380 --> 00:28:20,640
不管总统出了什么事
Whatever happens to the president,

476
00:28:20,640 --> 00:28:23,430
都不是你  或者我的错
it's not your fault, or mine.

477
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:26,880
-你以为我无关紧要吗  -我可没这么说
- You don't think I make a difference? - I didn't say that.

478
00:28:31,210 --> 00:28:33,030
还是你觉得我不够投入
You don't think that I'm dedicated enough?

479
00:28:33,030 --> 00:28:34,410
太投入了
Too dedicated.

480
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:37,520
过了就有问题了  会让你一叶障目
That can be a problem. That can make you blind.

481
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:39,310
你根本不知道
You have no idea...

482
00:28:46,330 --> 00:28:48,890
我做了不可原谅的事  莉安
I've done something unforgivable, LeAnn.

483
00:28:54,680 --> 00:28:55,610
什么
What?

484
00:28:58,530 --> 00:29:00,190
我杀了佐伊·巴恩斯
I killed Zoe Barnes.

485
00:29:00,990 --> 00:29:02,710
你为什么要这么说
Why would you say that?

486
00:29:14,060 --> 00:29:16,400
我只是想保护她
All I ever tried to do was keep her safe.

487
00:29:18,550 --> 00:29:20,690
她说她想就此消失
She said she wanted to be invisible.

488
00:29:22,310 --> 00:29:24,170
我知道这根本不可能
I knew it wasn't possible.

489
00:29:27,950 --> 00:29:30,360
我知道她要消失
I knew that she would only ever go away...

490
00:29:31,280 --> 00:29:32,730
就得我亲自动手
if I made sure of it.

491
00:29:37,520 --> 00:29:38,880
我不信你
I don't believe you.

492
00:29:39,780 --> 00:29:40,950
你当然信
Yes, you do.

493
00:29:44,500 --> 00:29:47,150
相信我  这是我活该
Believe me... I deserve this.

494
00:29:47,150 --> 00:29:49,450
佐伊·巴恩斯落轨被地铁撞死了
Zoe Barnes fell in front of a train.

495
00:29:49,450 --> 00:29:50,780
调查结果是意外事故
It was ruled an accident.

496
00:29:50,780 --> 00:29:54,000
是我把她从站台上推下去的  然后我就走了
I pushed her off the platform and I walked away.

497
00:30:16,750 --> 00:30:19,730
我知道你联系了布莉姬特·柯恩
I know you reached out to Bridget Cohen.

498
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:24,980
把我肝脏的来头告诉她或是委员会
Telling that committee or her how I got my liver

499
00:30:24,980 --> 00:30:29,450
对政府  对你  都没有一丝好处
is not going to help this administration or you.

500
00:30:30,450 --> 00:30:33,100
我告诉你做什么有好处
But here is what is going to help.

501
00:30:33,900 --> 00:30:36,190
我要你去找委员会
This is what you're going to tell that committee

502
00:30:36,370 --> 00:30:38,500
这么说道格·斯坦普
about Doug Stamper.

503
00:30:41,260 --> 00:30:42,760
你就住这儿
You actually live here?

504
00:30:43,380 --> 00:30:46,680
我不经常住
Well... I'm not here that much.

505
00:30:47,100 --> 00:30:48,770
偶尔让我朋友来住住
I let friends use it now and again.

506
00:30:49,140 --> 00:30:51,320
-谢谢你的谨慎  -应该的
- Thanks for your discretion. - Of course.

507
00:30:51,820 --> 00:30:53,130
我不会待太久
I won't be too long.

508
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:54,900
你慢慢来
Take your time.

509
00:30:55,280 --> 00:30:57,030
如果需要什么  我随叫随到
If you need anything, I'll be on call.

510
00:30:58,740 --> 00:30:59,860
他是讲道理的
He's reasonable.

511
00:31:01,110 --> 00:31:02,340
是啊  他必须这样
Yeah, he needs to be.

512
00:31:03,280 --> 00:31:04,580
他们也没怎么查
They didn't look that hard.

513
00:31:04,620 --> 00:31:06,920
特勤局知道我没什么好隐瞒的
The Secret Service knows I have nothing to hide.

514
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:08,600
他就在楼下
He's downstairs.

515
00:31:11,350 --> 00:31:12,570
别客气
Make yourself at home.

516
00:31:30,960 --> 00:31:32,900
我小时候可喜欢捉迷藏了
I used to love to hide as a kid.

517
00:31:34,100 --> 00:31:35,640
我总是藏得非常好
I was really good at it.

518
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:39,490
我总能找到最隐蔽的藏身处
I could always choose the best places.

519
00:31:41,500 --> 00:31:43,090
从来没被抓到过
Nobody ever found me.

520
00:31:46,790 --> 00:31:49,140
有一次大家干脆不玩了
One time, everybody just gave up.

521
00:31:50,490 --> 00:31:53,930
所以我在那儿躲了整整13个小时
So I stayed put for, like, 13 hours straight.

522
00:31:57,430 --> 00:31:58,520
你想要什么
What do you want?

523
00:32:02,010 --> 00:32:05,570
他说如果我同意  我绝不会后悔的
He said I wouldn't regret it... if I said yes.

524
00:32:07,650 --> 00:32:08,680
弗兰西斯
Francis.

525
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:11,310
就是想当初  我同意
When I agreed to write the book

526
00:32:11,420 --> 00:32:13,870
写他起家的故事的时候
about his origin story way back when.

527
00:32:15,820 --> 00:32:18,060
那他现在可后悔请你了
Well, he regrets asking you now.

528
00:32:18,810 --> 00:32:20,810
我同意  是因为我总是非常喜欢
I said yes 'cause I have always been a sucker

529
00:32:20,810 --> 00:32:24,360
听别人是怎么讲他们自己的
for what people tell themselves about themselves.

530
00:32:24,360 --> 00:32:26,200
谁还有手稿
Who has the manuscript?

531
00:32:29,640 --> 00:32:30,630
只有你
You do.

532
00:32:32,070 --> 00:32:33,640
出版商呢
And publishers?

533
00:32:34,850 --> 00:32:35,830
还没给
Not yet.

534
00:32:39,020 --> 00:32:40,640
所以你觉得如何
So what did you think?

535
00:32:42,770 --> 00:32:45,130
有好多段落你都划掉了  汤姆
There are huge sections blacked out, Tom.

536
00:32:45,130 --> 00:32:47,800
你把我们描绘成了怪物
