00:44:13,660 --> 00:44:15,420
哈维小姐  少跟我打感情牌
Ms. Harvey, please, spare me the semantics...

716
00:44:15,420 --> 00:44:16,940
-好吧  -我只需要你
- Okay, fine. - I just need you...

717
00:44:16,940 --> 00:44:19,320
他收集数据了吗  是的
Was he collecting data? Yes.

718
00:44:19,360 --> 00:44:22,560
他过界了吗  很可能
Did he cross a line? Most likely.

719
00:44:22,750 --> 00:44:24,840
我去看过他  看他的工作
I did visit with him, checking in on his work.

720
00:44:24,840 --> 00:44:28,150
你见过一屏的代码吗  电脑代码
Have you seen a screen of code? Computer code.

721
00:44:28,370 --> 00:44:29,890
那根本看不懂
It's indecipherable.

722
00:44:31,660 --> 00:44:33,930
赛斯·格雷森怎么最终没作证
Why did Seth Grayson end up not testifying?

723
00:44:33,930 --> 00:44:34,830
无可评价
No comment.

724
00:44:34,830 --> 00:44:36,090
我们听说他的证词
We heard that his testimony

725
00:44:36,090 --> 00:44:38,140
跟总统的幕僚长有关
had to do with the president's chief of staff.

726
00:44:38,140 --> 00:44:41,030
我很欢迎他来我们委员会作证
Who I would welcome testifying in front of our committee.

727
00:44:41,080 --> 00:44:44,140
我敦促道格·斯坦普和其他政府人员
I urge Doug Stamper and the rest of the administration

728
00:44:44,140 --> 00:44:46,720
别再躲在行政特权之后了
to stop hiding behind executive privilege.

729
00:44:47,140 --> 00:44:48,360
我们目前只知道
All we learned so far is that

730
00:44:48,360 --> 00:44:51,660
总统对他的白宫发生的事毫不知情
the president knew nothing about anything going on in his White House.

731
00:44:54,830 --> 00:44:56,180
一共六个人
There were six of them,

732
00:44:56,610 --> 00:44:57,900
他们轮流来
and they all took a turn.

733
00:44:58,700 --> 00:44:59,940
除了罗梅洛
Except for Romero.

734
00:45:00,380 --> 00:45:01,770
他只是看了
He only watched.

735
00:45:02,720 --> 00:45:04,410
至少他是这么跟校长说的
Or... at least that's what he told the dean.

736
00:45:05,780 --> 00:45:07,200
但我知道真相
But I know the real story.

737
00:45:08,110 --> 00:45:10,200
她叫罗谢尔
Her name was, uh, Rochelle.

738
00:45:10,740 --> 00:45:12,400
你不是没有他的把柄吗
I thought you had nothing on this guy.

739
00:45:12,400 --> 00:45:13,490
你知道多久了
How long have you known this?

740
00:45:13,490 --> 00:45:15,600
我是想留到我们需要的时候
I was holding it until... Or, if we needed it.

741
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:17,520
是你需要的时候吧
No, until you needed it, you mean.

742
00:45:17,850 --> 00:45:18,850
这没什么区别
Look, it makes no difference.

743
00:45:18,860 --> 00:45:20,150
我可能会用  可能不会
I might use it, I might not.

744
00:45:20,160 --> 00:45:21,530
但我还是想作证
But I still wanna testify.

745
00:45:21,530 --> 00:45:22,360
你现在作证
For you to testify now,

746
00:45:22,360 --> 00:45:24,160
抱歉  简直疯了
excuse me for saying it, it's crazy.

747
00:45:24,160 --> 00:45:25,940
你觉得疯了吗  克莱尔
Do you think it's crazy, Claire?

748
00:45:25,950 --> 00:45:28,820
-我想在他面前维护自己  -我们有证人
- I wanna defend myself against this guy. - We have witnesses.

749
00:45:28,820 --> 00:45:31,170
我们的证人  代理人  让他们说
Our witnesses, surrogates. Let it come from them.

750
00:45:31,170 --> 00:45:32,460
我觉得我能赢
I think I can win.

751
00:45:32,600 --> 00:45:34,010
或者我该等到我被参议院抛弃
Or maybe I should wait until I lose the Senate...

752
00:45:34,010 --> 00:45:35,210
我就是觉得还有别的办法
I just think there are other ways...

753
00:45:35,220 --> 00:45:37,830
如果你放弃行政特权
If you give up executive privilege,

754
00:45:37,830 --> 00:45:39,850
我们就丧失了筹码  完全没了
we lose leverage. We lose it all.

755
00:45:41,980 --> 00:45:43,880
告诉主席  我愿作证了
Tell the chair I'm ready to appear.

756
00:45:46,230 --> 00:45:49,270
你的证词可能对你妻子造成的伤害
I mean, the damage your testimony could do to your wife

757
00:45:49,270 --> 00:45:50,970
不值得冒险
is not worth the risk.

758
00:45:50,970 --> 00:45:53,490
我们就是要讨论它的价值
Its worth is what we're here to discuss.

759
00:45:54,010 --> 00:45:57,900
我不喜欢由我来说  但是
I... I don't appreciate being the one to tell you this, but...

760
00:45:58,510 --> 00:46:02,070
你的总统之位已经保不住了
your presidency is beyond repair.

761
00:46:04,070 --> 00:46:06,010
你不知道我接下来要做什么
You don't know what I'm going to do next.

762
00:46:06,010 --> 00:46:09,140
不是这个吗  这才是让你困扰的吧
Isn't that it? Isn't that what really bothers you?

763
00:46:09,160 --> 00:46:10,560
别以为我没从你加入的那一刻
Don't think I haven't been watching you

764
00:46:10,560 --> 00:46:12,730
就在观察你
from the moment you stepped on board.

765
00:46:13,070 --> 00:46:15,350
你满口承诺  戴维斯女士
You're full of promises, Ms. Davis.

766
00:46:15,740 --> 00:46:17,850
麦卡伦的事仍未平息
The information about Macallan is still out there

767
00:46:17,850 --> 00:46:21,280
而艾哈迈迪则神出鬼没
and Ahmadi is, oh, so elusive.

768
00:46:22,170 --> 00:46:23,440
你从走进我家
You've been sabotaging me

769
00:46:23,450 --> 00:46:26,410
就一直在给我捣乱
from the moment you stepped into my house.

770
00:46:28,240 --> 00:46:30,680
你不喜欢我  是吧
You don't care for me very much, do you?

771
00:46:31,650 --> 00:46:33,210
是的
No, I don't.

772
00:46:34,070 --> 00:46:35,910
我一点也不喜欢
I couldn't care less.

773
00:46:36,770 --> 00:46:39,340
但如果你让克莱尔开心  我就开心
But if you make Claire happy, that makes me happy.

774
00:46:39,340 --> 00:46:40,930
如果你能好好帮她
If you can help her,

775
00:46:41,530 --> 00:46:43,200
-那很好  -你愿付出什么
- good. - What's it worth to you?

776
00:46:44,800 --> 00:46:46,260
你打算做什么样的交易
Well, what kind of deal are we talking about?

777
00:46:46,260 --> 00:46:47,800
要我不作证
For me not to testify.

778
00:46:47,800 --> 00:46:49,630
我在华府外有人
Well, I have contacts outside the Beltway.

779
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:52,390
我可以给你找到各种肥差
I can set you up in any number of lucrative positions.

780
00:46:52,400 --> 00:46:53,360
不  那不够好
No, that's not good enough.

781
00:46:53,360 --> 00:46:55,100
谁都能给我那个
Anyone could offer me that.

782
00:46:56,730 --> 00:46:58,050
你说呢
You tell me.

783
00:46:58,070 --> 00:47:00,520
不不  不能这样
No, no, no. It's not going to work like that.

784
00:47:00,520 --> 00:47:02,660
你说你能为我做什么
You tell me what you can do for me.

785
00:47:02,660 --> 00:47:04,300
我接触过你这样的人
I've been around your kind.

786
00:47:04,770 --> 00:47:06,460
一般没接触到这种深度
Not usually at this level.

787
00:47:06,750 --> 00:47:08,460
但你就是忍不住
But you can't help yourself.

788
00:47:11,700 --> 00:47:14,190
给我开价  戴维斯女士
Make me an offer, Ms. Davis.

789
00:47:16,330 --> 00:47:19,240
你愿为她付出什么
What is she worth to you?

790
00:47:20,980 --> 00:47:22,160
很多
A lot.

791
00:47:27,100 --> 00:47:29,340
那么我是这么想的
So then here's what I'm thinking.

792
00:47:30,820 --> 00:47:32,210
你是否庄严宣誓确认
Do you solemnly swear and affirm

793
00:47:32,210 --> 00:47:33,950
你即将给出的证词是真相
that the testimony you are about to give is the truth,

794
00:47:33,950 --> 00:47:35,750
全部真相  绝无隐瞒
the whole truth, and nothing but the truth?

795
00:47:35,760 --> 00:47:36,890
我宣誓
I do.

796
00:47:37,360 --> 00:47:38,270
请记录
Let the record reflect that

797
00:47:38,270 --> 00:47:41,030
证人给出了肯定回答
the witness has answered in the affirmative.

798
00:47:42,370 --> 00:47:44,620
总统先生  我想感谢你前来作证
Mr. President, I want to thank you for appearing...

799
00:47:44,860 --> 00:47:46,300
希望我们可以为美国人民
and I hope we get to clear some things up

800
00:47:46,300 --> 00:47:47,550
澄清一些事
for the American people.

801
00:47:47,550 --> 00:47:49,540
总统先生  你可以开始
Mr. President, the floor is yours.

802
00:47:49,560 --> 00:47:51,630
你想讲多久都行
You can take as long or as short as you like.

803
00:47:51,630 --> 00:47:53,620
如果你有书面声明
If you have any written statement,

804
00:47:53,630 --> 00:47:56,940
我们会在稍后将它纳入记录
we will include it after and it will be part of the record.

805
00:47:57,650 --> 00:47:59,150
总统先生  请讲
Mr. President, you are recognized.

806
00:47:59,150 --> 00:48:00,920
谢谢  主席先生
Thank you, Mr. Chairman...

807
00:48:01,520 --> 00:48:04,200
也感谢其他委员会成员
and to the other members of this committee.

808
00:48:05,100 --> 00:48:08,500
我今天同意在委员会面前作证
I have agreed to appear before this committee today...

809
00:48:08,780 --> 00:48:10,300
是因为
because...

810
00:48:11,010 --> 00:48:12,740
我有罪
I'm guilty.

811
00:48:18,900 --> 00:48:23,370
我花了30年的人生
Guilty of having spent the last 30 years of my life

812
00:48:23,370 --> 00:48:24,500
在这里
here...

813
00:48:24,720 --> 00:48:26,460
在国会
in this Congress.

814
00:48:26,870 --> 00:48:28,380
在众议院
In this House.

815
00:48:28,920 --> 00:48:31,750
然后成为副总统  总统
Then as vice president and now as president,

816
00:48:31,750 --> 00:48:34,870
只为效力于人民
trying to do the people's work.

817
00:48:35,070 --> 00:48:38,980
委员会指控我犯下了很多事
Now, this committee has accused me of a great number of things.

818
00:48:38,980 --> 00:48:42,950
你们指控我贿赂
You accused me of pay to play.

819
00:48:42,950 --> 00:48:47,680
那么我也指控你们犯下了同样罪行
And so I accuse you of exactly the same.

820
00:48:47,790 --> 00:48:52,470
我还指控你们只为自己的利益行使政治手段
I also accuse you of playing politics only when it suits you.

821
00:48:53,930 --> 00:48:55,760
你们都拿了钱
You're all being paid.

822
00:48:55,870 --> 00:48:58,540
你们都有要效力的主子
You're all serving some master.

823
00:48:58,540 --> 00:49:00,480
你们每个人
Each and every one of you,

824
00:49:00,480 --> 00:49:03,780
你们知道我所言不虚
and you know I know that for a fact.

825
00:49:03,780 --> 00:49:07,120
比如你  罗梅洛议员
You, for example, Congressman Romero...

826
00:49:07,420 --> 00:49:11,810
你扳倒我的不懈努力  是为了正义吗
and your crusade to take me down, is it for justice?

827
00:49:12,050 --> 00:49:13,990
为了国家吗
For the good of the nation?

828
00:49:14,010 --> 00:49:18,000
你真的是想要真相吗
Is the truth what you're really after?

829
00:49:18,000 --> 00:49:20,830
还是为了个人利益
Or is it for some personal gain?

830
00:49:20,830 --> 00:49:23,210
或许是为了填补
Perhaps to try to fill

831
00:49:23,210 --> 00:49:26,180
你很久之前卖掉的
the small hole in your soul

832
00:49:26,180 --> 00:49:30,530
那一块灵魂留下的空洞
that you sold off a long time ago?

833
00:49:30,530 --> 00:49:33,000
-总统先生  -不  不  不
- Mr. President. - No, no, no.

834
00:49:33,000 --> 00:49:35,260
这是我的开场陈述
This is my opening statement,

835
00:49:35,260 --> 00:49:37,300
我要说完
and I will give it in full.

836
00:49:37,300 --> 00:49:40,460
我还没说完  女士们先生们
I am not done, ladies and gentlemen.

837
00:49:42,220 --> 00:49:45,110
你们指控我违反规则
You accuse me of breaking the rules,

838
00:49:45,110 --> 00:49:49,380
我告诉你们  我完全遵守规则
and I tell you, I am playing by the rules.

839
00:49:49,380 --> 00:49:54,270
正是你们和我一起达成的规则
The very rules that you and I all agreed upon.

840
00:49:54,270 --> 00:49:57,350
正是你们和我
The very rules that you and I

841
00:49:57,350 --> 00:50:00,480
一起写的规则
all wrote together.

842
00:50:00,660 --> 00:50:02,260
是的  我非常有罪
So, yes, I'm guilty as hell,

843
00:50:02,260 --> 00:50:04,140
但你们也都有罪
but then so are all of you.

844
00:50:04,290 --> 00:50:06,320
是的  体制有问题
Yes, the system is corrupt,

845
00:50:06,320 --> 00:50:09,430
但你们想要我这样的人守门
but you wanted a guardian at the gate like me.

846
00:50:09,430 --> 00:50:10,370
为什么呢
And why?

847
00:50:10,370 --> 00:50:11,800
因为你们知道
Because you know

848
00:50:11,800 --> 00:50:15,580
我会不惜一切
I will do whatever it takes.

849
00:50:15,860 --> 00:50:19,550
你们都喜欢这样
And you have all enjoyed it,

850
00:50:19,550 --> 00:50:23,990
参与其中  并从中获利
been party to it and benefited by it.

851
00:50:24,590 --> 00:50:26,490
别否认  你喜欢的
Don't deny it. You've loved it.

852
00:50:26,680 --> 00:50:28,990
你并不需要我坚持什么
You don't actually need me to stand for anything.

853
00:50:28,990 --> 00:50:31,020
你只希望我站出来
You just need me to stand.

854
00:50:31,630 --> 00:50:33,190
希望我强势
To be the strong man.

855
00:50:33,190 --> 00:50:35,090
希望我采取行动
The man of action.

856
00:50:35,270 --> 00:50:39,780
天呐  你好喜欢行动和口号
My God, you're addicted to action and slogans.

857
00:50:39,780 --> 00:50:41,640
不管我说了什么
It doesn't matter what I say.

858
00:50:41,640 --> 00:50:42,950
我做了什么
It doesn't matter what I do.

859
00:50:42,950 --> 00:50:45,230
只要我有所作为
Just as long as I'm doing something,

860
00:50:45,230 --> 00:50:47,720
你就乐意跟着走
you're happy to be along for the ride.

861
00:50:47,920 --> 00:50:50,600
老实说  我不怪你
And frankly, I don't blame you.

862
00:50:50,760 --> 00:50:53,230
你生活中有那么多愚蠢和犹豫
With all the foolishness and indecision in your lives,

863
00:50:53,230 --> 00:50:55,320
为什么不要个我这样的人
why not a man like me?

864
00:50:55,430 --> 00:50:57,230
我不道歉
I don't apologize.

865
00:50:57,990 --> 00:51:01,110
最终  我不在意你是爱我还是恨我
In the end, I don't care whether you love me or you hate me,

866
00:51:01,110 --> 00:51:03,270
只要我赢就行
just as long as I win.

867
00:51:03,720 --> 00:51:07,210
结局早被安排好  规则是被操纵的
The deck is stacked. The rules are rigged.

868
00:51:11,080 --> 00:51:14,680
欢迎来到理智时代的终结
Welcome to the death of the Age of Reason.

869
00:51:15,800 --> 00:51:20,290
已经没有是非了
There is no right or wrong. Not anymore.

870
00:51:20,760 --> 00:51:22,810
只有入局
There's only being in...

871
00:51:24,180 --> 00:51:26,360
和出局
and then being out.

872
00:51:30,020 --> 00:51:32,850
所以我不要再参与其中了
So I will not be party to this any longer.

873
00:51:32,960 --> 00:51:37,280
我不要再替你们背负骂名了
I will not wear the target for any of you anymore.

874
00:51:37,280 --> 00:51:41,470
你们都已经利用我太久了
You have all used me far long enough.

875
00:51:41,470 --> 00:51:44,240
所以派对结束  旅程结束
So, the party's over, the ride's done.

876
00:51:44,240 --> 00:51:45,820
我太尊重这一职位
I respect the office too much

877
00:51:45,820 --> 00:51:47,940
不能允许这继续下去
to allow this to continue going on.

878
00:51:47,970 --> 00:51:51,270
所以我要向委员会和全国人民宣布
That's why I am announcing to this committee and to the nation

879
00:51:51,270 --> 00:51:53,580
明晚6点起
that as of 6:00 p.m. tomorrow evening,

880
00:51:53,580 --> 00:51:57,760
我将辞去美国总统一职
I shall resign the office of President of the United States.

881
00:51:59,150 --> 00:52:00,090
秩序
Order!

882
00:52:00,250 --> 00:52:04,830
届时我乐意回答你们的一切问题
And I will be happy to take any questions you may have.

883
00:52:05,170 --> 00:52:08,840
但我的直觉是  已经没那个必要了
But my gut tells me that isn't really going to be necessary.

884
00:52:09,050 --> 00:52:19,050
{\an5}{\pos(193,150)}听证会作证有两个类型
一种要求证人宣誓  宣誓后如果说谎  就是违法行为
另一种不宣誓  有不实之言不用负法律责任
如果被发现宣誓后说谎  可能被国会表决定为"蔑视国会"
但位高权重之人  往往也只受到书面谴责  并不一定真的会被起诉
普通人则不敢冒险
国会有发传票的权力  收到传票的人按法律规定需要服从
但如果不服从  并不会直接受到惩罚
往往是  如果在接受调查时不配合  那么可能会导致司法介入
然后走法律程序  被起诉定罪
同样  如果国会在调查后发现被调查者有违法行为
那么相关的司法部门会随即介入  进行进一步的起诉  定罪
也就是说  国会调查很严重  但并不能代替法律程序

